        "description": "I used to love George Lopez. His stand-up was witty, cultural, and funny as hell. Unfortunately, he has lost a couple of steps in his later years. Mr. Lopez no longer has the charisma that he once exhibited and his material was a bit boring and at times, his speech was difficult to understand. He wore a bucket hat throughout the show which looked super goofy and not cool in any sense. At the end of the show, he took the hat off to show his long gray ponytail that he apparently is very proud of. In addition, the Hard Rock venue located at Universal Studios was extremely inconvenient to get to. The parks were packed with people, masses of whom were exiting at the time that we were coming in. We were literally fighting swarms of sweaty theme park goers, most of whom had been there all day…ughh. Leaving three stars is being optimistic. I was hoping for a five star show, however, as Neil Diamond once sung, “used-to-be’s don’t count anymore, they just lay on the floor til we sweep them away.”",
        "datePublished": "2026-03-31T15:42:47Z",
        "author_name": "CeeJay",
        "ratingValue": 3,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
