    "reviews": [
      {
        "title": "Best concert we've ever seen",
        "description": "We are a concert goer family! Averaging 4-5 concerts a year. This still tops our charts as the best concert ever. The energy was unreal. Amazing music. Great opener. My 4 year old and 14 year old went and both had a BLAST! Cant wait to see them again",
        "datePublished": "2026-03-21T19:02:01Z",
        "author_name": "Alicia",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "They played 'Selene' and I literally ascended to heaven",
        "description": "As someone who's followed them since the Speak To Me EP days, hearing deep cuts like 'Selene' and '30 Lives' live was EVERYTHING. Dan's vocal control during the bridge of 'Release' was insane. The extended drum solo in 'Thunder' with that Hell and Silence EP transition?? GENIUS. Wayne did the guitar slide from the original 'Curse' demo and I lost it. True fans know. Best setlist curation I've seen in 47 shows. 🐉⚡",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-10T06:09:14Z",
        "author_name": "ThunderstrikeB3liever2012",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "Demons broke me in the best possible way 😭✨",
        "description": "I'm literally writing this through tears in my car because I can't drive yet. When they played Demons and Dan held that note, I completely lost it. The elderly woman next to me handed me tissues and we both just sobbed together. The way the entire arena lit up like stars during Birds... I've never felt so connected to 20,000 strangers. My mascara is RUINED and my soul is HEALED. Thank you ID for making me feel less alone. 💫",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-09T20:17:39Z",
        "author_name": "TequilaxStarboy69",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "MY EARS ARE STILL RINGING AND MY MIND IS SHATTERED (IN A GOO",
        "description": "Y'ALL I HAVE NEVER BEEN TO A CONCERT BEFORE AND I AM LITERALLY QUESTIONING EVERYTHING?! The way Dan Reynolds APPEARED from BENEATH THE STAGE like some kind of music deity?! I screamed so loud I lost my voice before they even finished Thunder. The floating platforms during Whatever It Takes had me ASCENDING. I've been watching concert videos in my bedroom for years but NOTHING prepared me for this sensory overload of pure magic 🤯✨ Currently ordering tickets to 5 more shows bye",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-09T10:11:14Z",
        "author_name": "concertvirginnomore",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "From Classical Piano to THUNDER - My Mind is Shattered!",
        "description": "Y'ALL. As someone who's only ever been to piano recitals (I played for 12 years), I was NOT prepared for Dan Reynolds to literally defy gravity?! The moment Bones started, my classical music brain short-circuited in the best way 🤯 The pyrotechnics made my heart stop, and I think I ascended to another dimension during Believer. Currently googling how to become a professional concert-goer because my piano teacher would be SHOOK. Sorry Mozart, I'm an ID convert now! 🎹➡️🎸",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-09T03:14:08Z",
        "author_name": "BassDropBetty_98",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "Reluctantly Admitting Commercial Success Can Have Artistic M",
        "description": "As someone who typically gravitates toward obscure Estonian post-rock, I entered with skepticism. But Dan Reynolds' vocal control on 'Demons' was legitimately impressive, and the polyrhythmic breakdown in 'Whatever It Takes' showed genuine musicianship. Yes, it's mainstream, but their live sound engineering is actually *chef's kiss*. The acoustic rendition of 'Bones' demonstrated they're not just Pro Tools merchants. My indie cred is shamefully compromised, but excellence must be acknowledged.",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-09T00:28:14Z",
        "author_name": "vinyl_elitist_but_whatever",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "From 'Meh' to MEGA Fan in One Night!",
        "description": "Ok so I only knew Radioactive and Bones before this show (my friend dragged me along). But HOLY MOLY y'all - I've had their entire discography on repeat for 2 weeks straight now! Dan Reynolds did a backflip while hitting that high note in Whatever It Takes and I literally ascended 😱 The thunder effects during Thunder rattled my dental fillings in the best way possible. Currently teaching my cat to sing Demons. Send help, I'm obsessed! 🐉✨",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-08T21:23:39Z",
        "author_name": "AccidentalDragonling",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "Amazing show but security confiscated my trail mix!?",
        "description": "Dan Reynolds' energy was absolutely infectious and the production value was mind-blowing. Thunder literally gave me chills! But seriously, who classifies trail mix as an 'outside food security threat'? Had to buy $14 nachos instead. Still an incredible night though - the way they mixed Bones with Warriors was pure genius. Just pack light and leave your supposedly dangerous nuts and dried fruit at home lol",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-08T19:13:25Z",
        "author_name": "ConcertSnackSneaker",
        "ratingValue": 4,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "Amazing show but why is hand sanitizer $12??",
        "description": "The concert was absolutely incredible and Dan Reynolds' energy was through the roof! Thunder literally gave me chills. BUT can we talk about the $12 hand sanitizer at the merch booth?? Like I know inflation is real but come on 😭 Still giving 5 stars because Bones and Enemy back to back made me forget about my overpriced clean hands. Security was super nice too and let me keep my chapstick collection in my purse!",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-08T18:45:46Z",
        "author_name": "ChapstickHoarder_82",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      },
      {
        "title": "300+ Shows Later, These Dragons Still Surprised Me",
        "description": "Been hitting concerts since The Police's Synchronicity tour in '84. Seen everyone from Zeppelin reunions to Pearl Jam marathons, but ID's production value? Next level stuff. The floating platforms during 'Whatever It Takes' put Pink Floyd's wall to shame. Dan Reynolds has the stamina of Bruce Springsteen in his prime, and that thunder-sync during 'Thunder' rattled my veteran bones in the best way. Worth every penny of my social security check 😂",
        "datePublished": "2025-09-08T15:44:58Z",
        "author_name": "RockShowSage_Since1984",
        "ratingValue": 5,
        "bestRating": 5
      }
    ]
  }
